      <p>Any post or goods delivered to the Space or documents served at the Space ["Post"] and addressed to the Skiff Mate or the Skiff Mates business or related interests are the Skiff Mates responsibility. The Skiff reserves the right to dispose of Post left for longer than one calendar month. The Skiff reserves the right to refuse to accept delivery of Post on behalf of the Skiff Mate. The Skiff Mate is responsible for all Post addressed to them or their business or related interests whether they took actual delivery or not. Skiff Mates are asked to quickly collect Post. The Skiff is not responsible for notifying the Skiff Mate if any Post arrives for them. The Skiff is in no way responsible for any loss or damage etc resulting in lost, unaccepted or uncollected Post.</p>
      <h2>18. Pets</h2>
      <p>Whilst we don't want to be spoilsports, we're mindful of allergies and phobias and so ask that pets are kept at home and not bought into the Space without prior Agreement. Guide dogs are permitted.</p>
      <h2>19. Food and Drink </h2>
      <p>Skiff Mates are asked to be mindful that this is a community and people focused Space and that consumption of food and drink should be reasonable and not infringe on other Skiff Mates enjoyment of the Space. </p>
      <h2>20. Notices</h2>
      <p>Any notice given under this Agreement shall be sent by email and include hello@theskiff.org. Notice shall be deemed served at the time of delivery. </p>
